---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
const updated = '2026-07-17';
---

<BaseLayout title="Cookie Policy" description="How VisaLang uses URL state and browser local storage." noindex={true}>
  <main class="page-shell">
    <article class="guide-article narrow-page">
        <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
        <h1>Cookie Policy</h1>
        <p class="guide-summary">Last updated: {updated}</p>

        <h2>What are cookies</h2>
        <p>Cookies are small text files stored in your browser. VisaLang does not currently set first-party cookies through its site code.</p>

        <h2>Local storage we use</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Advertising:</strong> VisaLang does not currently set advertising cookies or load an advertising network. No advertising consent mechanism is currently active.</li>
          <li><strong>Tool result URLs:</strong> after a tool successfully generates a result, it places only the non-sensitive values needed to restore that result in the page URL. Current tools do not store their form fields in local storage. URLs can remain in browser history or be included when a link is copied.</li>
          <li><strong>Route progress:</strong> route pages can store the current route step in browser local storage. This storage also has no site-defined automatic expiry.</li>
          <li><strong>Guide filters:</strong> Guide Library filters also use page URL values so the filtered view can be restored or shared.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Third-party social tracking</h2>
        <p>We do not use third-party social-media tracking cookies. Third-party sites you visit from VisaLang, including official sources and advertising destinations, apply their own policies.</p>

        <h2>Managing cookies</h2>
        <p>Use “Restart this tool” to remove that tool’s URL values. You can also clear or block local storage in your browser settings; doing so may remove saved route-step progress. No advertising preference control is shown while advertising remains disabled.</p>

        <h2>Third-party embeds</h2>
        <p>VisaLang does not currently load third-party video or resource embeds. Following a link to an external site takes you to that site, where its own privacy and cookie policies apply.</p>

        <h2>Questions or changes</h2>
        <p>For privacy questions, use our <a href="/contact/">contact page</a>. We update this page when our cookie, consent, analytics, or advertising approach changes.</p>

        <p class="compliance-line">See also our <a href="/privacy-policy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>
        <p class="last-updated">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </article>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
